Sr. Director, Product & Service Innovation




    

        posted July 15, 2017
      

Marriott International, Inc.
      Bethesda, MD
    
Apply

Share:

Email

Facebook


Tweet


LinkedIn

























About This Job



Description
Marriott International is the world’s largest hotel company, with more brands, more hotels and more opportunities for associates to grow and succeed. We believe a great career is a journey of discovery and exploration. So, we ask, where will your journey take you?
Requirements
JOB SUMMARY
The mission of the CX Innovation team is to deliver
innovations that ensure our enterprise and brands are differentiated, relevant,
and competitive. We lead by discovering insights, developing concepts and
developing prototypes for major initiatives and high profile projects. We
collaborate with internal and external partners and monitor in-market
performance of new initiatives to ensure the successful build and deployment
of breakthrough concepts. We are a
part of the Customer Experience Discipline that focuses on driving
customer-centricity throughout Marriott.
The Senior Director, Product and Service innovation
serves as a key leader within the CX Innovation team focused on applying and
evolving innovation strategies which connect service, the hotel environment and
the digital, ultimately enabling connected and compelling consumer experiences
at the property, portfolio and enterprise levels. This position will lead
diverse projects with portfolio and enterprise impact, closely collaborating
with the VP, Product & Service Innovation and VP Digital Innovation, as
well as cross-disciplinary leaders and teams within and beyond BMSC. Ensuring
brand, operational and digital experience integrity for both on and above
property experiences, this role will also contribute to the design and adoption
of new processes, tools and strategies which contribute to the broader mission
of the CX team as a cutting-edge COE for innovation, style and experience
design excellence. A key focus area will be elevating enterprise efforts to
foster a culture of innovation across teams, disciplines and continents, a
shared charge across leadership. As a project leader, the role requires the
ability to understand the diverse needs of stakeholders across the business,
apply a deep understanding of consumer, market and consumer trends, coordinate
team members while shepherding the innovation process from insights to concepts
and prototypes, addressing operational and digital dimensions while pushing for
disruptive, new thinking and solutions which stretch our brands, disciplines
and company.
This position develops strategy for key brand
projects, synthesize the results of detailed research efforts across a variety
of platforms, creates unique, operational concepts that reflect market and
consumer preference, and provides an innovation lens to market-based
initiatives across the Marriott International enterprise. This position
plays a key role in high priority project coordination, long range strategic
planning of portfolio wide initiatives, as well as ‘end to end’ concept design
and activation. This role will have hands-on involvement for concept activation
in high priority hotels and reflects Marriott International’s emphasis on and
commitment to design leadership, operations integration and results of high
integrity. 
CANDIDATE
PROFILE 
Education and Experience 
BA/BFAMBA
or advanced degree preferred.World
Class experience in two or more of the following - Innovation,
Hotel Operations, Product/Service Design, Digital design8+
years of professional experience, demonstrating progressive career growth and a
pattern of exceptional performance in innovation, design, creative, branding,
hotel operations, or business strategy.
REQUIRED:
Strong leadership
skills that inspire team confidence and respect.Proficiency
in human-centered design process (Design Thinking)Excellent
personnel management skills, with the ability to nurture the development of
both creative and analytical people.Proven ability
to build and foster relationships.Excellent
team player, with the ability to collaborate effectively with partners, project
managers, art directors.Experience
interpreting trends and research to design and implement innovative products
and services that support brand visionSolid ability
to manage multiple stakeholders and influence the direction of product design
& development.Ability to
problem-solve and leverage resources to optimize department capabilitiesPossess
knowledge of cutting edge design solutions with an ability to pull inspiration
from a variety of input streams.Ability to
present to internal and external audiences, as well as listen openly to
feedback, with the end result of achieving the best work Assesses
consumer insights, brand positioning and market challenges; sees the points of
differentiation and weaves a clear, concise direction that becomes the basis
for inspiring the creative product Strong analytical skills and experienceAbility to
work on cross-functional team.
Technical
& Creative Skills
Experience
within a brand organization or design agency creating transactional products in
a consumer-facing market, preferably with experience working on projects for
the hospitality industry Effective
project management skills with an ability to manage multiple projects
simultaneously, develop accurate cost estimates, and manage to a budgetMust possess
