The Via Less Traveled: Wind Your Way Through Italy's Jaw-Dropping Hill TownsSandwiched between Rome and Florence, an almost mythical swath of earth exists -- one where low-rolling, vine-clad hills are crowned by centuries-old villas; stone-house-clustered towns are perched atop mountains; and the gently twisting roads make reality seem like an endless car commercial.

